<h2>Network testing</h2>
A common routine required in applications is a simple test to check for internet
connectivity. Libraries such as Closure test by attempting to load a one pixel clear image. If it load successfully one can conclude that the connection is available. 

<div  class="code-block console-wrap">
<div class="code-block code" >
<code class="PHP">

var networkTester = new goog.net.NetworkTester(function(isOnline) {
    var msg = isOnline ? 'I am online - time to catch up on blogs!' 
            : 'I am offline - I guess I will find a book to read.';
    log(msg);
});
networkTester.setTimeout = 13;
networkTester.setNumRetries =100;


// The start() method must be called to kick off network testing.
networkTester.start();

</code>
